by stof at 2013-03-30T16:55:18Z

Instead of the 2 options and making them incompatible with the ``name`` argument, I suugest the following signature:

- ``container:debug`` shows the list of services
- ``container:debug foo`` shows the ``foo`` service
- ``container:debug --parameters`` shows the list of parameters
- ``container:debug foo --parameters`` shows the ``foo`` parameter

This would mean that the ``--parameters`` is toggling the command from services to services, and the argument is still used to pass the name. And it would mean you don't need 2 options to support parameters but only one.

The same change could then be applied to the support of tags

What do you think about it ?

